                    android:layout_marginBottom="8dp"
                    android:paddingLeft="50dp"
                    android:paddingRight="50dp"
                    android:text="The structure of a For Loop is quite different than the other loops, the structure goes like this - (instantiation; condition; incrementation) First the value to be incremented is instantiated, then the limit for that value is set, and then the value of the incrementation is set. Like the While Loop and Do While structure the For Loop runs the code inside the curly braces. However in the case of a For Loop, a counter variable is unnecessary as the int i acts as a counter. The code stops when the limit is reached. "
